  "palo-alto": "Palo Alto sits at the epicenter of EV adoption in the United States, with Tesla's headquarters nearby and a population that embraced electric vehicles earlier than almost any other city. Public charging infrastructure is dense throughout downtown and near Stanford University, and the city has installed chargers in municipal parking structures for decades. Palo Alto's charging network is among the most mature in the country.",

  "santa-monica": "Santa Monica's beachfront location and progressive environmental policies have made it a leader in EV infrastructure on the westside of Los Angeles. Charging stations are available at the Santa Monica Place mall, city parking structures along the promenade, and near the beach. The city has prioritized accessible charging as part of its broader sustainability agenda.",

